Class Manuscript

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • model.Manuscript

  • public class Manuscript
extends java.util.Observable
    Manuscript stores the manuscripts to be submitted to a Conference. It stores fields of a unique ID number, a User author, the conference it belongs to, a file name, a file, a tag informing the User if it has been submitted, it's recommendation status (given by the Sub-Program Chair), it's final recommendation status (given by the Program Chair), the Sub-Program Chair this manuscript is assigned to, and a list of Reviewers to review the manuscript.
    Version:
    2 June 2014
    Author:
    Trevor Jennings

    • Constructor Detail

      • Manuscript

        public Manuscript(int theID,
          User theAuthor,
          Conference theConference,
          java.lang.String theFileName,
          java.io.File theFile,
          Status theRecommendStatus,
          Status theFinalStatus,
          boolean theIsSubmitted)
        Constructor creates Manuscript object that currently has persistent data in the database i.e. this Manuscript has been created before in a previous Session. Therefore, it accepts an ID as a parameter rather than having to create a new one.
        Parameters:
        theID - the Manuscripts unique ID number.
        theAuthor - the Manuscript's User author.
        theConference - the Conference this Manuscript belongs to.
        theFileName - the String filename of this Manuscript.
        theFile - the File for this Manuscript.
        theSPC - the User Sub-Program Chair this Manuscript is assigned to.

      • Manuscript

        public Manuscript(User theAuthor,
          Conference theConference,
          java.lang.String theFileName,
          java.io.File theFile)
        Constructor creates Manuscript object that currently has does not have persistent data in the database i.e. this Manuscript is being created for the first time. Therefore, an ID must be generated and assigned. This is done by calling the createConference() method from ManuscriptControl, which returns an integer, representing the Manuscript's ID.
        Parameters:
        theID - the Manuscripts unique ID number.
        theAuthor - the Manuscript's User author.
        theConference - the Conference this Manuscript belongs to.
        theFileName - the String filename of this Manuscript.
        theFile - the File for this Manuscript.
        theSPC - the User Sub-Program Chair this Manuscript is assigned to.
